	<Title>
		Chocolate: Does it impair calcium absorption?
	</Title>
	<Abstract>
		Chocolate contains oxalate &amp;mdash; a naturally occurring compound in cocoa beans, which can inhibit calcium absorption.
	</Abstract>
	<Question>
		A friend told me that chocolate impairs absorption of calcium. Is this true?
	</Question>
